      "comment": "BUNDABERG GUM (7) goes very well here starting 13 times for five wins and five minors. Placed last time (19.46) at Hobart in a Grade 4, finishing third and beaten 3.5 lengths. Makes strong appeal on best. BONTA (2) was safely held last time out, finishing sixth at Hobart over 340m behind Fishing Yari (20.06) in a Grade 5. Remains without a win from the draw but has been in the placings two times from three attempts. Will give the top chances plenty to think about. VERY SNEAKY (1) comes off an average run last start when fifth at Hobart over 340m behind Bland Option (19.75) in a Grade 5. Goes well out of this box with a win and two minor placings. Cannot be underestimated. HIGHGATE ROSIE (3) is building a nice sequence of placings and will be thereabouts again.",
